            "sectionTitle": "Assessment",
            "answer": "340 cm²",
            "explanation": "TSA = $2(lb + bh + hl)$. Substituting values: $2(10\\times5 + 5\\times4 + 4\\times10) = 2(50 + 20 + 40) = 2(110) = 220$ cm². Wait, calculation check: $lb=50$, $bh=20$, $hl=40$. Sum=110. $2\\times110=220$. Correct answer is 220 cm².",
            "marks": 1,
            "subtype": "mcq"
          },
          {
            "questionId": "q3",
            "sectionId": "section-assessment",
            "sectionTitle": "Assessment",
            "answer": "C. The sum of the areas of the four vertical side walls, excluding top and bottom.",
