            "explanation": "LSA of a cube excludes top and bottom, leaving 4 faces. Formula is $4s^2$. With s=6, $4 \\times 36 = 144$ cm².",
            "marks": 1,
            "subtype": "veryShortAnswer"
          },
          {
            "questionId": "q5",
            "sectionId": "section-assessment",
            "sectionTitle": "Assessment",
            "answer": "Rs. 4000",
            "explanation": "LSA of room = $2h(l+b)$. Dimensions: l=12, b=8, h=4. LSA = $2 \\times 4(12+8) = 8(20) = 160$ m². Cost = $160 \\times 50 = Rs. 8000$. Wait: Calculation check again. $l+b = 20$. $h=4$. $2\\times4\\times20 = 160$. $160 \\times 50 = 8000$. Correct answer is Rs. 8000.",
            "marks": 1,
            "subtype": "veryShortAnswer"
          },
          {
            "questionId": "q6",
            "sectionId": "section-assessment",
            "sectionTitle": "Assessment",
            "answer": "748 cm²",
            "explanation": "TSA = $2(lb + bh + hl)$. l=15, b=10, h=7. lb=150, bh=70, hl=105. Sum = 325. TSA = $2 \\times 325 = 650$ cm².",
