            "sectionId": "section-assessment",
            "sectionTitle": "Assessment",
            "answer": "LSA excludes the top and bottom faces. A cube has 6 faces total ($6s^2$). LSA only counts the 4 side walls, so it is $4 \\times s^2$. The excluded faces are the base (bottom) and the lid (top).",
