            "answer": "(a) TSA = $2(300 + 150 + 200) = 6.7$ m²? No, cm units. l=20, b=15, h=10. lb=300, bh=150, hl=200. Sum=650. TSA=$2\\times650=1300$ cm². (b) LSA = $2h(l+b)$ for room (meters). l=20, b=15, h=8. Area = $2 \\times 8(35) = 16 \\times 35 = 560$ m². Explanation: We use LSA because painting walls excludes the floor and ceiling.",
            "explanation": "Part (a): Correct formula for TSA of cuboid applied to cm dimensions. Part (b): Correct identification of LSA application for wall painting with correct calculation in meters.",
